<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
        Phase 24.2e (ADR-017 §3.5) — Apple Push Notification service.

        `aps-environment` value = "production":
            TestFlight builds use the production APNs gateway even though
            they are pre-release. The "development" value applies only to
            debugger-attached local builds (Xcode → Run on device with
            development provisioning profile). Hardcoding "production"
            here matches the closed-beta TestFlight distribution path.
            Local debugger push test is deferred to Phase 24.4+ if real
            demand surfaces (would require a Configuration-conditional
            xcconfig switch + per-config entitlements path).

        Capability: ensure the App ID `io.github.b150005.skeinly`
        registered in Apple Developer Portal has the "Push Notifications"
        capability enabled, AND the Distribution Provisioning Profile
        embedded in the IPA includes that capability. Both must align
        with this entitlement value or `xcodebuild` reports a code-sign
        mismatch at archive time.

        **On-device debug push test is unsupported by design**: a
        debug-signed local build on a physical device using the
        development APNs gateway (`api.development.push.apple.com`)
        will fail registration here with "No valid 'aps-environment'
        entitlement string found" — the failure is handled gracefully
        (nil token, 30s timeout) so there is no crash, but the token
        callback will never fire. Tester push QA happens via TestFlight
        only. Phase 24.4+ may revisit if a local-debug push iteration
        path becomes necessary (would require xcconfig-conditional
        APS_ENVIRONMENT + per-config entitlements paths).
    -->
    <key>aps-environment</key>
    <string>production</string>

    <!--
        Phase 39 (W3 / 2026-05-11) — Universal Links via Associated Domains.

        `applinks:b150005.github.io` declares that this app handles
        https://b150005.github.io/* URLs as Universal Links. iOS fetches
        `https://b150005.github.io/.well-known/apple-app-site-association`
        on first launch (and periodically thereafter) to verify the
        domain claims the app via `appIDs: ["L9ZR4679P5.io.github.b150005.skeinly"]`.
        Path matching (which subpaths the app handles) is encoded in
        the AASA `components` array, NOT here — this entitlement only
        gates "may we claim links from this domain at all".

        URL family handled (per the W3 deep-link audit, 2026-05-10):
          /skeinly/patterns/shared/<token>   — share token deep link
          /skeinly/patterns/<patternId>      — public pattern detail
          /skeinly/pull-requests/<prId>      — pull request detail

        Other paths fall through to Safari (web fallback HTML at
        docs/public/skeinly/* — deferred to post-alpha polish).

        Capability: ensure the App ID `io.github.b150005.skeinly`
        registered in Apple Developer Portal has the "Associated
        Domains" capability enabled (provisioning profile screenshot
        2026-05-10 confirms ON), AND the Distribution Provisioning
        Profile includes that capability. The Path Y fastlane sigh
        refactor (commit 0956d3f) handles capability propagation
        automatically — re-Generate the profile in Apple Developer
        Portal once after capability changes; next CI run picks up
        the updated profile.
    -->
    <key>com.apple.developer.associated-domains</key>
    <array>
        <string>applinks:b150005.github.io</string>
    </array>
</dict>
</plist>
